export const title = "Usage";
export const description = "How to use React Native Vector Icons components, props, and image sources";
export const body = "Learn how to use icon components, customise their appearance, and generate bitmap images.\n\n## Icon Component\n\nYou can use one of the bundled icon sets or roll your own custom font. Import the icon family you need:\n\n### Bundled Import (with dynamic loading)\n\n```jsx\nimport { FontAwesomeFreeSolid } from \"@react-native-vector-icons/fontawesome-free-solid\";\n\n<FontAwesomeFreeSolid name=\"rocket\" size={30} color=\"#900\" />\n```\n\n### Static Import (smaller bundle)\n\nIf you do not need [dynamic font loading](./advanced#dynamic-font-loading), use the `/static` import for a slightly smaller bundle size:\n\n```js\nimport { FontAwesomeFreeSolid } from \"@react-native-vector-icons/fontawesome-free-solid/static\";\n```\n\n### Inline Example\n\n```jsx\nimport { Text } from \"react-native\";\nimport { Ionicons } from \"@react-native-vector-icons/ionicons/static\";\n\nconst ExampleView = (props) => (\n  <Text>\n    Lorem <Ionicons name=\"book\" color=\"#4F8EF7\" /> Ipsum\n  </Text>\n);\n```\n\n## Props\n\nIcon components accept any [Text prop](https://reactnative.dev/docs/text.html#props) plus the following:\n\n| Prop | Description | Default |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `size` | Size of the icon. Can also be passed as `fontSize` in the style object. | `12` |\n| `name` | Which icon to show. See the [Icon Directory](./directory) to browse available icons. | None |\n| `color` | Colour of the icon. | Inherited |\n\n## Styling\n\nSince `Icon` builds on top of the `Text` component, most [style properties](https://reactnative.dev/docs/style.html) work as expected. Useful properties include:\n\n`backgroundColor`, `borderWidth`, `borderColor`, `borderRadius`, `padding`, `margin`, `color`, `fontSize`\n\nBy combining these you can create rounded icon buttons, bordered icon badges, and more.\n\n## Usage as PNG Image / Source Object\n\nA convenient way to use icons in components that rely on bitmap images rather than scalable vector icons. You need to use Expo (with `expo-font` installed) _or_ install `@react-native-vector-icons/get-image`.\n\nBoth methods return an `ImageResult` object (`{ uri, width, height, scale }`) that can be passed directly as an `Image` source.\n\n### Synchronous\n\n```jsx\nconst source = Icon.getImageSourceSync('user', 20, 'red');\n// or with an options object:\nconst source = Icon.getImageSourceSync('user', { size: 20, color: 'red', lineHeight: 28 });\n\nreturn <Image source={source} />;\n```\n\n> [!WARNING]\n> `getImageSourceSync` is blocking and might incur performance penalties. Subsequent calls use a cache.\n\n### Asynchronous\n\n```js\nconst source = await Icon.getImageSource('user', 20, 'red');\n// or with an options object:\nconst source = await Icon.getImageSource('user', { size: 20, color: 'red' });\n```\n\n## Static Methods\n\nAll static methods from `Icon` are supported by multi-styled fonts.\n\n| Method | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| `getImageSource` | Returns a promise resolving to an `ImageResult` of a bitmap version of the icon. `const source = await Icon.getImageSource(name, { size, color, lineHeight })` |\n| `getImageSourceSync` | Same as `getImageSource` but synchronous. `const source = Icon.getImageSourceSync(name, { size, color, lineHeight })` |";
